records.addlTxt:
Defendant Alec J Brazeau in court with attorney Matthew Huppertz.   District Attorney's Office Law Intern appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant pleads no-contest to Counts 2 and 3.  Count 1 is dismissed and read-in.  Court imposed the following sentence:

The Defendant was sentenced to the following:

IMPOSED AND STAYED SENTENCE OF AS TO COUNT 2:   

2 YEARS IMPRISONMENT 
  -  1 YEAR OF INITIAL CONFINEMENT
  -  1 YEAR OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION;

TERM OF PROBATION:  3 YEARS;

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:  
*AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
*Absolute Sobriety;  Random U.A.'s ; 
*No Use or Possession of alcohol, controlled substances or drug paraphernalia.
*No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
*Any valid prescription drugs must be taken only in the manner in which they are prescribed.
*Inform Agent of all prescriptions
*Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
*Maintain full-time employment and/or combination of schooling 
*No contact with:  Wales Elementary, Wales Elementary personnel and/or the co-actors
*DNA sample to be provided if not yet previously done.

RESTITUTION:  to be determined;

COURT COSTS:  $268.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation);

DNA SURCHARGE:  $250.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation);

Defendant to perform 40 hours of community service each year of probation; 

DRGOD: $10.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation); 

CONDITION TIME: 45 days, STAYED; to be used at agent's discretion.  Agent to determine with or without non working hours.  

IF REVOKED:
Defendant is eligible for Challenge Incarceration Program.
Defendant is not eligible for Substance Abuse Program.

Felony warnings, voting rights and firearms warnings given.

Expunction is conditionally granted upon verification of completion of sentence, payment of all costs/fees and no new criminal law violations.

Defendant was sentenced as to Count 3:

9 months County jail.  First 60-days straight time (3 days credit), then 4 months Huber released for work and/or school, then 3 months Day Report.  

Defendant waived right to expunction as to Count 3. 

COURT COSTS:  $243.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation);

DRGOD:  $10.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation);

DNA Surcharge:  waived as to Count 3.
